'''Manuel Ugarte Ribeiro''' ({{IPA|es|maˈnwel uˈɣaɾte}}; born 11 April 2001) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{English football updater|ManchesU}} club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]]. Primarily a defensive midfielder, he can also be played as a [[central midfielder]].

Ugarte came through [[Centro Atlético Fénix|Fénix]]'s youth academy, being promoted to the first-team in 2016. In December 2021, he joined Portuguese [[Primeira Liga]] club [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]]. Following an impressive half-season, Ugarte signed for fellow Primeira Liga club [[Sporting CP]], winning the [[Taça da Liga]] in his time with the club. In July 2023, he joined [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] for a transfer worth €60&nbsp;million. In August 2024, he joined Manchester United for a fee of €50&nbsp;million.

Ugarte is a former youth international for Uruguay, representing the country at [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Uruguay Olympic football team|under-23]] levels. He made his senior international debut in 2021. He represented Uruguay at the [[2024 Copa América]] and was named in the [[Copa América awards#Team of the Tournament|Team of the Tournament]].

==Club career==
===Fénix===
Born in [[Montevideo]], Ugarte started his football career in the youth ranks of local club City Park, before joining [[Centro Atlético Fénix|Fénix]]'s youth setup, being promoted to the first-team at the age of 15 by manager Rosario Martínez.<ref name="Earlycareer">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sporting.pt/pt/futebol/equipa-principal/plantel/manuel-ugarte-ribeiro|title=Biografia – Manuel Ugarte Ribeiro|date=9 August 2021 }}</ref> Shortly after, he was included in the 30-man to compete in the [[2016 Copa Sudamericana]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lista de 30 y concentración|url=https://www.tenfield.com.uy/lista-de-30-y-concentracion/|website=Tenfield|date=7 August 2016|access-date=4 October 2022|language=es}}</ref> 

Ugarte made his professional debut on 4 December 2016, replacing [[Agustín Canobbio]] in the 83rd minute in a 4–1 league win against [[Danubio F.C.|Danubio]].<ref name="prodebut">{{cite web|title=Fénix vs. Danubio – 4 December 2016 – Soccerway|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2016/12/04/uruguay/primera-division/centro-atletico-fenix/danubio-futbol-club/2347263/|accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref> By doing so, he became the youngest ever player in the 21st century to play professionally in [[Uruguay]] (aged 15 years and 233 days).<ref name="prodebut"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Con la frente bien alta|url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/ovacion/futbol/frente-alta.html|website=Diario EL PAIS Uruguay|date=5 December 2016|access-date=4 October 2022|language=es}}</ref> Initially Ugarte played as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]], before being converted to a [[midfielder]].<ref name="Earlycareer"/>

Under [[Juan Ramón Carrasco]], Ugarte was entrusted to play more regularly, being named club captain aged 18 and scoring his first goal on 10 March 2019 in a 2–0 win against [[Racing Club de Montevideo|Racing Club]], as he went on to make 14 appearances in the [[Uruguayan Primera División]].<ref name="firstgoal">{{cite web|title=Fénix vs. Racing|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/03/10/uruguay/primera-division/centro-atletico-fenix/racing-club-de-montevideo/2983904/|date=10 March 2019|access-date=5 January 2020}}</ref> On 29 October 2020, Ugarte assisted [[Luciano Nequecaur]] goal in the ''albivioletas'' 3–1 over [[Club Deportivo Huachipato|Huachipato]] in the first leg of the [[2020 Copa Sudamericana]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Un partidazo: Manuel Ugarte Crack Sigue Rompiendo Fénix|trans-title=Manuel Ugarte, the crack that follows breaking in Fénix|url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/ovacion/futbol/copa-sudamericana-partidazo-manuel-ugarte-crack-sigue-rompiendo-fenix.html|website=[[El País (Uruguay)|El País Uruguay]]|date=29 October 2020|access-date=4 October 2022|language=es}}</ref> Overall, he made 57 appearances for the club and scored one goal.<ref>{{Cite web|title=New player of the champion: the Uruguayan Manuel Ugarte passes to Sporting|url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/nuevo-jugador-del-campeon-el-uruguayo-manuel-ugarte-pasa-al-sporting-33466834|accessdate=3 October 2022|website=[[OneFootball]]|date=29 July 2021 }}</ref>

===Famalicão===
On 29 December 2020, Ugarte signed a five-year contract with Portuguese club [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]] for a fee of €3&nbsp;million for 80% of his economic rights.<ref name="fam1">{{cite web|title=Manuel Ugarte Assina por cinco épocas|date=29 December 2020|url=https://www.fcfamalicao.pt/manuel-ugarte-assina-por-cinco-epocas/|access-date=29 December 2020}}</ref><ref name="fam2">{{cite web|title=Oficial: Manuel Ugarte é o primeiro reforço de inverno do Famalicão|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/famalicao/detalhe/oficial-manuel-ugarte-e-o-primeiro-reforco-de-inverno-do-famalicao|accessdate=29 December 2020|archive-date=7 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307205823/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/famalicao/detalhe/oficial-manuel-ugarte-e-o-primeiro-reforco-de-inverno-do-famalicao|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his [[Primeira Liga]] debut on 17 January 2021, playing the entire 2–0 victory at [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]].<ref name="Earlycareer"/> On 21 February, he scored his first goal for the club in a 1–0 victory over [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Famalicão vs Rio Ave|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/amp/jogos-em-direto-13374183.html|website=[[Diário de Notícias]]|date=21 February 2021|language=pt|archive-date=14 August 2023|access-date=23 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814123308/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/amp/jogos-em-direto-13374183.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Despite initially not being a starter, Ugarte eventually earned a place in the team under manager [[Ivo Vieira]], as his versatility enabled him to play in various positions in midfield, which was found useful by his coach, as Famalicão narrowly missed on European qualification to the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa Conference League|Europa Conference League]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Filipe|last=Balreira|title=Ugarte como uma fénix: Do clube de bairro à afirmação no Sporting e o sonho de ser economista|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/ugarte-como-uma-fenix-do-clube-ao-bairro-ao-estrelato-no-fm-e-a-afirmacao-nos-leoes|website=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|date=4 April 2022|language=pt|access-date=23 April 2022|archive-date=27 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230427035657/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/ugarte-como-uma-fenix-do-clube-ao-bairro-ao-estrelato-no-fm-e-a-afirmacao-nos-leoes|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Ugarte, a fénix uruguaia com apetite de leão|url=https://www.msn.com/pt-pt/desporto/futebol/ugarte-a-f%C3%A9nix-uruguaia-com-apetite-de-le%C3%A3o/ar-AAMMXOI|publisher=[[MSN]]|language=pt}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
On 9 August 2021, Ugarte signed a five-year contract with [[Sporting CP]] of the same league, for a fee of €6.5&nbsp;million for half of his economic rights.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Oficial: Manuel Ugarte é Reforço do Leão|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2021-08-09/sporting-oficial-manuel-ugarte-e-reforco-do-leao/900483|website=[[A Bola]]|date=9 August 2021|access-date=9 August 2021|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Adérito|last=Esteves|title=Sporting: Ugarte já assinou e é anunciado segunda-feira|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/transferencias/liga/sporting-ugarte-ja-assinou-e-e-anunciado-segunda-feira|website=Mais Futebol|date=9 August 2021|language=pt}}</ref> On 14 August, he made his debut for the club, replacing [[João Palhinha]] in the 92nd minute in a 2–1 away win against [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] in the Primeira Liga.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Ugarte: "Muito feliz pela minha estreia no Sporting"|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/ugarte-muito-feliz-pela-minha-estreia-no-sporting|website=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|date=7 August 2021|archive-date=6 October 2022|access-date=23 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006204316/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/ugarte-muito-feliz-pela-minha-estreia-no-sporting|url-status=dead}}</ref> Ugarte scored his first goal for Sporting on 2 January 2022, opening the 2–1 home victory over his former club Famalicão.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Ugarte estreia-se a marcar com a camisola do Sporting... mas não festeja|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/sporting-famalicao-ugarte-abriu-assim-o-marcador-veja-o-golo-14260249.html|website=[[O Jogo]]|date=26 October 2021|language=pt|archive-date=20 December 2022|access-date=23 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221220092803/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/sporting-famalicao-ugarte-abriu-assim-o-marcador-veja-o-golo-14260249.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Initially signed as back-up to João Palhinha, following the latter's injury, Ugarte began having a run as starter, with manager [[Ruben Amorim]] entrusting him Palhinha's place on 3 December in the 3–1 away victory against rivals [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in the [[Lisbon derby]].<ref name="dispute1">{{Cite web|title=Crescimento de Ugarte ameaça titularidade de Palhinha|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1909635/crescimento-de-ugarte-ameaa-titularidade-de-palhinha|website=Notícias a O Minuto|date=13 January 2022|language=pt}}</ref><ref name="dispute2">{{Cite news|title=Ugarte Aperta Cada Vez Mais Palhinha|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-03-24/sporting-ugarte-aperta-cada-vez-mais-palhinha/933470|website=[[A Bola]]|date=24 March 2022|language=pt}}</ref> His impressive performances and quick adaptation to the team earned him praise from his manager, as he began to play more regularly and threaten Palhinha's starting position.<ref name="dispute1"/><ref name="dispute2"/> In the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League]] group stage, Ugarte had the most tackles and interceptions combined at 34, including 12 tackles in a 3–0 away win against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Who is Manuel Ugarte? The ball winning Sporting star linked with Tottenham|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Articles/ciAxHUtFb0e1mMDFOJ0RqA/Show/Who-is-Manuel-Ugarte-The-ball-winning-Sporting-star-linked-with-Tottenham|website=WhoScored|date=16 October 2022}}</ref>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
On 15 June 2023, in an interview with Portuguese newspaper [[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|''Record'']], Ugarte confirmed that he would be joining [[Ligue 1]] side [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Manuel Ugarte confirms move to PSG – Get French Football News|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/manuel-ugarte-confirms-move-to-psg/|website=Get Football News France|date=15 June 2023}}</ref> On 7 July 2023, PSG officially announced that he had joined the club on a five-year contract until 30 June 2028.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Manuel Ugarte au Paris Saint-Germain|url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/manuel-ugarte-au-paris-saint-germain-jusquen-2028|website=PSG|date=7 July 2023|language=fr}}</ref> The transfer fee was reported to be €60&nbsp;million, with PSG triggering Ugarte's release clause.<ref>{{Cite news|title=PSG : Manuel Ugarte est Parisien ! (officiel)|url=https://www.onzemondial.com/transferts/psg-manuel-ugarte-est-parisien-officiel-836626|date=7 August 2023|website=Onze Mondial|language=fr}}</ref> He made his debut in a 0–0 draw against [[FC Lorient|Lorient]] at the [[Parc des Princes]] on 12 August.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Paris Saint-Germain V Lorient |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202324/paris-saint-germain-v-lorient|website=PSG|date=12 August 2023}}</ref> 

In August 2023, Ugarte was one of three nominees for the [[UNFP Player of the Month]] award.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ugarte in contention for UNFP August Player of the Month award |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/ugarte-in-contention-for-unfp-august-player-of-the-month-award-38213871|website=OneFootball|date=13 October 2023|access-date=25 September 2023}}</ref> In his first four Ligue 1 matches, he registered 41 ball recoveries, the most in the league. The only player bettering Ugarte's statistic after the first four Ligue 1 matches of the season since the 2006–07 season was former PSG midfielder [[Thiago Motta]] with 47 ball recoveries.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 September 2023 |title=La stat impressionnante de Manuel Ugarte qui le rapproche d'un record d'une légende du PSG en Ligue 1 |url=https://www.90min.com/fr/posts/la-stat-impressionnante-de-manuel-ugarte-qui-le-rapproche-d-un-record-d-une-legende-du-psg-en-ligue-1 |access-date=2023-09-25 |website=90min.com |language=fr}}</ref> For his performances in August and September, Ugarte was described as a "revelation" of PSG's early season by ''[[Le Parisien]]'' and ''[[L'Équipe]].''<ref>{{Cite news|title=«Il comprend le jeu» : Manuel Ugarte décrypté avant PSG – OM |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Les-caracteristiques-de-manuel-ugarte-psg-decryptees/1421548|website=L'Équipe|access-date=25 September 2023|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first1=Marc|last1=Mechenoua|first2=Benjamin|last2=Quarez|title=PSG : sur les traces de Manuel Ugarte, l'enfant prodige de Montevideo |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/psg-sur-les-traces-de-manuel-ugarte-lenfant-prodige-de-montevideo-19-09-2023-BOOVYMUJ5ZCWLINT6XBEPK4NKA.php|website=[[Le Parisien]]|date=19 September 2023|access-date=25 September 2023|language=fr}}</ref> However, after the first two months of the season, Ugarte progressively lost his place as a starter. It was reported in the media that manager [[Luis Enrique]] deemed that he did not correspond to his style of play.<ref>{{Cite web |title="Ugarte doit partir en prêt pour progresser" – 100% PSG, le billet – France Bleu |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/emissions/100-psg-le-billet/ugarte-doit-partir-en-pret-pour-progresser-100-psg-le-billet-7416911 |access-date=2024-07-18 |website=ici par France Bleu et France 3 |date=28 June 2024 |language=fr}}</ref> Ugarte would make frequent appearances as a substitute for the rest of the season, amid occasional starts.<ref>{{Cite web |title=D'inamovible à joueur de rotation, que se passe-t-il pour Ugarte au PSG ? {{!}} Flashscore.fr |url=https://www.flashscore.fr/actualites/football-ligue-1-d-inamovible-a-joueur-de-rotation-que-se-passe-t-il-pour-ugarte-au-psg/hnCNtdQh/ |access-date=2024-07-18 |website=www.flashscore.fr |language=fr}}</ref> PSG went on to complete a domestic treble by winning Ligue 1, the [[Coupe de France]], and the [[Trophée des Champions]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 May 2024 |title=PSG outwit Lyon to claim Coupe de France and domestic treble |url=https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20240525-psg-outwit-lyon-to-claim-coupe-de-france-and-domestic-treble |access-date=2024-07-18 |publisher=Radio France Internationale |language=en}}</ref> 

=== Manchester United ===
Ugarte signed for [[Premier League]] side [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 30 August 2024, signing a five-year contract with an option for a year extension.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transfer news: United sign Ugarte |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/transfer-news-manuel-ugarte-signs-from-psg |access-date=2024-08-30 |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |language=en}}</ref> The transfer fee was reported to be €50&nbsp;million, potentially increasing to €60&nbsp;million with add-ons.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=30 August 2024 |title=Manuel Ugarte joins Manchester United and promises to 'fight for trophies' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/aug/30/manuel-ugarte-join-manchester-united-and-promises-to-fight-for-trophies |access-date=2024-12-30 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He made his debut for United on 14 September, appearing for 17 minutes in a 3–0 win over [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 September 2024 |title=Southampton vs Manchester United 2024/25 |url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/115864 |publisher=Premier League}}</ref>

On 22 February 2025, Ugarte scored his first goal for Manchester United, an equaliser after coming from 2–0 down, helping his team draw 2–2 with [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] in United's final match at [[Goodison Park]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Douglas |first=Steve |date=22 February 2025 |title=Man United rallies to draw 2–2 at Everton in Premier League after late VAR drama |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/man-united-rallies-draw-2-144112950.html |website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref>

On 17 April 2025, Ugarte netted the opening goal in the [[2024-25 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] quarter-final second-leg against [[Olympique Lyon|Lyon]], with United eventually progressing after a dramatic 7–6 victory on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/maguires-121st-minute-winner-sends-man-utd-through-europa-league-semis-2025-04-17/#:~:text=MANCHESTER%2C%20England%2C%20April%2017%20(,Lyonnais%20in%20their%20quarter%2Dfinal | title=Maguire's 121st minute winner sends Man Utd through to Europa League semis | work=Reuters | date=17 April 2025 | last1=Hall | first1=Peter }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Ugarte earned five [[Cap (sport)|caps]] for Uruguay at [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|under-20 level]].<ref>{{cite web |title=5 – Manuel Ugarte – AUF |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/5-manuel-ugarte/ |website=auf.org.uy |access-date=14 September 2024 |language=es}}</ref> On 29 December 2019, [[Uruguay Olympic football team|Uruguay under-23]] team head coach [[Gustavo Ferreyra]] named Ugarte in the 23-man final squad for the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gustavo Ferreyra definió el plantel para el Torneo Preolímpico 2020|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/gustavo-ferreyra-definio-el-plantel-para-el-torneo-preolimpico-2020/|access-date=29 October 2020}}</ref> He made five appearances in the competition,<ref>{{cite web |title=Manuel Ugarte – AUF |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/manuel-ugarte/ |website=auf.org.uy |access-date=14 September 2024 |language=es}}</ref> scoring in a 1–1 draw against [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil]] in the final stage that helped Uruguay to finish third place.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sub-23 Brasil 1–1 Uruguay |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/preolimpico-2020-brasil-uruguay-fecha2-cuadrangular-final/ |website=auf.org.uy |date=6 February 2020 |access-date=14 September 2024 |language=es}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 5 March 2021, Ugarte was named in Uruguay senior team's 35-man preliminary squad for [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifying matches]] against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=35 futbolistas reservados para enfrentar a Argentina y Bolivia por Eliminatorias|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/35-futbolistas-reservados-para-enfrentar-a-argentina-y-bolivia/|website=[[Uruguayan Football Association]]|date=5 March 2021|access-date=7 March 2021|language=es}}</ref> However, [[CONMEBOL]] suspended those matches the next day amid concern over the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CONMEBOL suspends March World Cup qualifiers after clubs' refusal to release players|url=https://www.espn.in/football/blog-fifa/story/4330687/conmebol-suspends-march-world-cup-qualifiers-after-clubs-refusal-to-release-players|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=6 March 2021|access-date=7 March 2021}}</ref> He made his senior team debut on 5 September 2021, by coming on as a 70th-minute substitute for [[Matías Vecino]] in a 4–2 win against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=¿Por qué se fue llorando Manuel Ugarte del partido contra Bolivia?|url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/por-que-se-fue-llorando-manuel-ugarte-del-partido-contra-bolivia--2021960818|website=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador Uruguay]]|date=6 September 2021|access-date=6 September 2021|language=es}}</ref>

On 15 November 2024, Ugarte scored his first senior international goal, scoring in the 90+11th minute in 2026 World Cup qualifying against [[Colombian national football team|Colombia]], the latest scored winning goal in the CONMEBOL World Cup qualifying history.<ref>{{cite news |title=Man Utd's Ugarte scores dramatic late Uruguay winner |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c1jrkr4wzrno |website=BBC Sport |date=16 November 2024 |access-date=16 November 2024 |language=en}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, Ugarte was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Ugarte is a combative [[defensive midfielder]]. His strengths include his ability to win back possession with well timed tackles and defensive positioning. During the [[2023–24 Ligue 1]] season, he topped the charts for the most tackles, 98, despite playing only 25 league games out of a possible 34 league games as compared to other players.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manuel Ugarte to Man Utd? N'Golo Kante-like ball-winner could help shore up Erik ten Hag's midfield |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11096/13183322/manuel-ugarte-to-man-utd-ngolo-kante-like-ball-winner-could-help-shore-up-erik-ten-hags-midfield |access-date=2024-07-24 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

